  <static seed="101" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems50.pg">
    <statement><p>Jerry and Teresa are sharing a pizza. Jerry ate <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of the pizza, and Teresa ate <m>{{\frac{1}{8}}}</m> of the pizza. How much more pizza did Jerry eat than Teresa?</p>
<p>Jerry ate <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> more of the pizza than Teresa ate.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{24}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To find the difference of two numbers, we use subtraction:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{1}{6}}} - {{\frac{1}{8}}} 
      \amp = \frac{1 \cdot 4}{6 \cdot 4}-\frac{1 \cdot 3}{8 \cdot 3} \\
      \amp = \frac{4}{24} - \frac{3}{24} \\
      \amp = \frac{4-3}{24} \\
      
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{24}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Jerry ate <m>{{\frac{1}{24}}}</m> more of the pizza than Teresa ate.</p>
</solution>
